				There's another way to do this...the way they mention assumes you want to add spices after you cook it.  <br />
<br />
Shuck the corn.  Then add a dollop or two of butter to the corn, add salt and pepper, and then wrap it in wax paper. THEN put it in the microwave for a few minutes.  You will then have perfectly buttered and seasoned corn.			</div>
			
