				Seven minutes in a microwave?  Can't be.  The ONLY way to cook corn on the cob is to husk it, take off the remaining silk, put it into a pot of boiling water and immediately turn off the heat under the water.  In three minutes you're good to go.  Overcooking spoils corn.  (As it does all vegetables.)			</div>
			
