			<div class="comment_body">
				<div class="comment_time">
					4 hours ago ( 4:03 PM)				</div>

																												
				Wrong.<br />
<br />
Cook them in a microwave for 5 minutes per ear depending upon the wattage of the oven.  Leave the husk on and remove from the oven and let set for several minutes.  Pull back the husk and the silk comes off easily.  The husk also makes a great handle to hold the corn if you don't cut it off.<br />
<br />
Eat the corn in rows going up or down the length of the ear and not across unless you intend to leave a lot of the corn on the ear when done.<br />
<br />
We learned to use our microwave oven 20 years ago when we saw the instructions in the cookbook that came with a new oven.<br />
<br />
Leaving the husk on keeps the ears juicy and locks in the flavor.  The silk peels off easily when cooked.<br />
<br />
Take it from someone who grew up in a corn state.			</div>
			
